The paper deals with learning from web data, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of category-level supervision, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, making cs.IR and cs.CL likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper uses benchmark datasets, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM), making it a possible sub-category.
